<TITLE> 'Gas export move will be thwarted' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, Oct 9 (bdnews24.com)Gas will not be allowed to export at any rate, a pressure group of left-leaning politicians and professionals warned on Friday. "We have got no objection to foreign companies exploring and extracting gas from sea beds," Mohammad Shahidullah, convenor of the National Committee on Protection of Oil, Gas, Mineral Resources, Power and Ports said "But we will mount resistance if exports are made," he said at the divisional convention of the committee. Bimal Biswas, general secretary of Workers' Party of Bangladesh. said "Gas has to be used in our own mills and factories power plants." "The country's resources have to be used for its own use." Khulna district convenor Sheikh Moniruzzaman Moni presided over the convention. 
